# HOW BUILD IMAGE IN BLUEMIX REGISTER #

Link: https://console.ng.bluemix.net/docs/containers/container_images_building.html

## Requirements ##

1. Setup Docker, Cloud Foundry and Cloud Foundry Plugin

https://console.ng.bluemix.net/docs/containers/container_cli_cfic_install.html

2. Login to Bluemix

```sh
cf login [-a api.ng.bluemix.net]
```

cf will request to enter email and password

3. Initalize cf ic

```sh
cf ic init
```

and declare Env variables.

4. Create tag into Bluemix's register

```sh
docker tag <current_image_name_or_ID>:<optional_tag> <private_Bluemix_repository>/<new_image_name>:<optional_tag>
```

**Example**

```sh
docker tag training/sinatra registry.DomainName/my_namespace/new_sinatra
```

5. Build image and push to bluemix

```sh
cf ic build -t registry.ng.bluemix.net/<private_Bluemix_repository>/<image_name> <Directory with Dockerfile>
```

**Example**

```sh
cf ic build -t registry.ng.bluemix.net/mellody/curl curl
```